1
00:00:01,210 --> 00:00:03,378
(WHOOSHING)

2
00:00:11,512 --> 00:00:14,598
I wonder what's wrong with her.
She's sort of queasy.

3
00:00:15,933 --> 00:00:19,311
-Indigestion. Like she didn't want to land.
-If you think there's gonna be trouble,

4
00:00:19,436 --> 00:00:22,523
we could always get back inside
and go somewhere else.

5
00:00:27,402 --> 00:00:30,948
I think we've landed inside a cupboard.
Here we go.

6
00:00:31,698 --> 00:00:33,909
Open door 15.

7
00:00:33,992 --> 00:00:35,661
Some sort of base.

8
00:00:35,786 --> 00:00:39,122
Moon base, sea base, space base.
They build these things out of kits.

9
00:00:39,206 --> 00:00:42,125
Glad we're indoors.
Sounds like a storm out there.

10
00:00:42,251 --> 00:00:43,585
Open door 16.

11
00:00:45,379 --> 00:00:47,464
Human design,
you've got a thing about kits.

12
00:00:47,548 --> 00:00:51,718
This place was put together like a flat-pack
wardrobe, only bigger and easier.

13
00:00:51,802 --> 00:00:55,264
-Open door 17.
-Oh, it's a sanctuary base!

14
00:00:55,347 --> 00:00:57,391
-Close door 17.
-Deep-space exploration.

15
00:00:57,474 --> 00:00:59,685
We've gone way out. And listen to that.

16
00:00:59,768 --> 00:01:00,978
(HUMMING)

17
00:01:01,061 --> 00:01:03,480
Underneath. Someone's drilling.

18
00:01:04,648 --> 00:01:06,483
"Welcome to hell.”

19
00:01:06,608 --> 00:01:10,571
-Oh, it's not that bad.
-No, over there.

20
00:01:14,324 --> 00:01:15,993
Hold on.

21
00:01:16,076 --> 00:01:17,995
What does that say?

22
00:01:23,292 --> 00:01:25,502
That's weird. It won't translate.

23
00:01:25,836 --> 00:01:30,090
But I thought the Tardis
translated everything, writing as well.

24
00:01:30,173 --> 00:01:32,342
-I should see English.
-Exactly.

25
00:01:33,260 --> 00:01:36,597
Now if that's not working, then it means...

26
00:01:36,680 --> 00:01:38,890
this writing is old.

27
00:01:39,641 --> 00:01:41,393
Very old.

28
00:01:42,352 --> 00:01:44,021
Impossibly old.

29
00:01:44,104 --> 00:01:45,939
We should find out who's in charge.

30
00:01:46,023 --> 00:01:49,234
We've gone beyond the reach of
the Tardis' knowledge. Not a good move.

31
00:01:49,359 --> 00:01:51,737
-And if someone's looking for...
-Open door 189.

32
00:01:52,362 --> 00:01:54,656
Right, hello. Sorry.

33
00:01:55,115 --> 00:01:57,534
I was just saying, nice place.

34
00:01:57,618 --> 00:01:59,369
We must feed.

35
00:01:59,453 --> 00:02:01,580
-You gotta what?
-We must feed.

36
00:02:01,663 --> 00:02:04,499
-Yeah, I think they mean us.
-We must feed.

37
00:02:05,208 --> 00:02:06,543
We must feed.

38
00:02:06,793 --> 00:02:08,545
We must feed.

39
00:02:08,879 --> 00:02:10,547
We must feed.

40
00:02:10,672 --> 00:02:12,382
We must feed.

41
00:02:12,507 --> 00:02:15,093
We must feed. We must feed.

42
00:02:15,385 --> 00:02:18,347
We must feed. We must feed.

43
00:02:18,555 --> 00:02:21,266
We must feed. We must feed.

44
00:02:24,895 --> 00:02:27,397
(DOCTOR WHO THEME)

45
00:03:04,101 --> 00:03:05,769
We must feed...

46
00:03:07,437 --> 00:03:09,731
you, if you are hungry.

47
00:03:11,066 --> 00:03:13,318
-Sorry?
-We apologise.

48
00:03:13,735 --> 00:03:17,030
Electromagnetics have interfered
with speech systems.

49
00:03:17,572 --> 00:03:19,616
Would you like some refreshment?

50
00:03:20,575 --> 00:03:22,786
-Open door 18.
-Um...

51
00:03:24,037 --> 00:03:25,789
What the hell?

52
00:03:27,165 --> 00:03:28,458
How did...

53
00:03:34,214 --> 00:03:38,051
Captain, you're not gonna believe this.
We've got people.

54
00:03:38,135 --> 00:03:41,388
Out of nowhere.
I mean, real people. I mean...

55
00:03:41,471 --> 00:03:46,226
Two living people just standing here
right in front of me.

56
00:03:46,309 --> 00:03:49,104
(ON RADIO)
Don't be stupid, that's impossible.

57
00:03:49,187 --> 00:03:52,816
-I suggest telling them that.
-But you're a sort of space base.

58
00:03:52,941 --> 00:03:55,444
You must have visitors now and then.
It can't be that impossible.

59
00:03:55,527 --> 00:03:57,362
You telling me
you don't know where you are?

60
00:03:57,487 --> 00:03:59,906
No idea. More fun that way.

61
00:03:59,990 --> 00:04:04,661
(ON PA) Stand by, everyone. Buckle down.
We have incoming, and it's a big one.

62
00:04:04,786 --> 00:04:06,204
Quake 0.5 on its way.

63
00:04:06,329 --> 00:04:07,706
(ALARMS BLARING)

64
00:04:07,831 --> 00:04:11,334
Through here. Now.
Quickly, come on! Move!

65
00:04:15,005 --> 00:04:17,090
Move it! Come on!

66
00:04:19,176 --> 00:04:22,053
Keep moving! Come on! Keep moving!

67
00:04:35,525 --> 00:04:37,861
Oh, my God, you meant it.

68
00:04:38,278 --> 00:04:41,573
-People! Look at that, real people.
-That's us. Hurray!

69
00:04:41,656 --> 00:04:45,368
Yeah, definitely real.
My name's Rose, Rose Tyler,

70
00:04:45,452 --> 00:04:47,245
and this is the Doctor.

71
00:04:47,329 --> 00:04:52,626
Come on, the oxygen must be offline.
We're hallucinating, they can't be...

72
00:04:52,709 --> 00:04:56,254
-No, they're real.
-Come on, we're in the middle of an alert.

73
00:04:56,338 --> 00:04:59,883
Danny, strap up, the quake's coming in.
Impact in 30 seconds.

74
00:05:00,717 --> 00:05:03,970
Sorry, you two, whoever you are,
just hold on. Tight.

75
00:05:04,054 --> 00:05:06,807
-Hold on to what?
-Anything, I don't care, just hold on.

76
00:05:06,890 --> 00:05:08,558
Ood, are we fixed?

77
00:05:08,642 --> 00:05:11,895
Your kindness in this emergency
is much appreciated.

78
00:05:11,978 --> 00:05:15,106
-What's this planet called anyway?
-Don't be stupid. It hasn't got a name.

79
00:05:15,190 --> 00:05:17,400
How could it have a name?

80
00:05:17,484 --> 00:05:19,444
You really don't know, do you?

81
00:05:19,569 --> 00:05:21,571
And impact!

82
00:05:27,494 --> 00:05:29,412
Oh, well. That wasn't so bad...

83
00:05:42,008 --> 00:05:45,053
Okay, that's it. Everyone all right?

84
00:05:46,263 --> 00:05:47,931
Speak to me! Ida?

85
00:05:48,056 --> 00:05:49,099
-Yeah.
-Danny?

86
00:05:49,182 --> 00:05:50,475
-I'm fine.
-Toby?

87
00:05:50,600 --> 00:05:51,685
-Fine.
-Scooti?

88
00:05:51,768 --> 00:05:52,853
-No damage.
-Jefferson?

89
00:05:52,936 --> 00:05:53,979
Check!

90
00:05:54,062 --> 00:05:55,939
We're fine, thanks, fine.
Yeah, don't worry about us.

91
00:05:56,064 --> 00:06:00,443
Surface caved in.
I deflected it onto Storage 5 through 8.

92
00:06:00,527 --> 00:06:01,987
We've lost them completely.

93
00:06:02,112 --> 00:06:04,823
Toby, go and check the rocket link.

94
00:06:05,240 --> 00:06:06,700
That's not my department.

95
00:06:06,783 --> 00:06:08,743
Just do as I say, yeah?

96
00:06:13,707 --> 00:06:17,961
IDA: Oxygen holding.
Internal gravity at 56.6.

97
00:06:18,086 --> 00:06:20,130
We should be okay.

98
00:06:20,213 --> 00:06:22,632
Never mind the earthquake, that's...

99
00:06:23,550 --> 00:06:26,636
That's one hell of a storm.
What is that, a hurricane?

100
00:06:26,720 --> 00:06:29,806
You need an atmosphere for a hurricane.
There's no air out there.

101
00:06:29,890 --> 00:06:31,266
It's a complete vacuum.

102
00:06:31,349 --> 00:06:32,976
Then what's shaking the roof?

103
00:06:33,059 --> 00:06:36,897
You're not joking. You really don't know.

104
00:06:37,522 --> 00:06:40,442
Well, introductions.

105
00:06:40,901 --> 00:06:43,486
FYI, as they said in the olden days.

106
00:06:43,653 --> 00:06:46,197
I'm Ida Scott, Science Officer.

107
00:06:46,281 --> 00:06:49,910
Zachary Cross Flane, Acting Captain, sir.

108
00:06:50,201 --> 00:06:53,038
You've met Mr Jefferson,
he's Head of Security.

109
00:06:53,330 --> 00:06:55,707
Danny Bartock, Ethics Committee.

110
00:06:55,832 --> 00:06:57,667
Not as boring as it sounds.

111
00:06:57,751 --> 00:07:00,587
And that man who just left,
that was Toby Zed,

112
00:07:00,670 --> 00:07:03,423
Archaeology, and this...

113
00:07:03,506 --> 00:07:06,343
is Scooti Manista, Trainee Maintenance.

114
00:07:07,093 --> 00:07:08,470
And this...

115
00:07:10,263 --> 00:07:11,640
This is home.

116
00:07:12,807 --> 00:07:14,726
Brace yourselves.

117
00:07:14,809 --> 00:07:17,312
The sight of it sends some people mad.

118
00:07:40,293 --> 00:07:42,295
That's a black hole.

119
00:07:42,379 --> 00:07:44,422
But that's impossible.

120
00:07:44,506 --> 00:07:45,924
I did warn you.

121
00:07:46,007 --> 00:07:47,884
We're standing under a black hole.

122
00:07:48,051 --> 00:07:50,136
-In orbit.
-We can't be.

123
00:07:50,220 --> 00:07:53,056
IDA: You can see for yourself.
We're in orbit.

124
00:07:54,933 --> 00:07:56,309
But we can't be.

125
00:07:56,393 --> 00:08:00,397
This lump of rock is suspended
in perpetual geostationary orbit

126
00:08:00,480 --> 00:08:03,775
around that black hole, without falling in.

127
00:08:04,067 --> 00:08:05,151
Discuss.

128
00:08:05,986 --> 00:08:07,904
And that's bad, yeah?

129
00:08:08,989 --> 00:08:12,534
Bad doesn't cover it.
A black hole's a dead star.

130
00:08:12,617 --> 00:08:16,413
It collapses in on itself, in and in and in,
until the matter's so dense and tight,

131
00:08:16,496 --> 00:08:18,665
it starts to pull everything else in, too.

132
00:08:18,748 --> 00:08:21,084
Nothing in the universe can escape it.

133
00:08:21,167 --> 00:08:23,878
Light, gravity, time,

134
00:08:23,962 --> 00:08:27,757
everything just gets
pulled inside and crushed.

135
00:08:28,133 --> 00:08:30,677
So they can't be in orbit?

136
00:08:30,760 --> 00:08:33,304
-We should be pulled right in.
-We should be dead.

137
00:08:33,388 --> 00:08:36,141
And yet, here we are.

138
00:08:36,683 --> 00:08:38,977
Beyond the laws of physics.

139
00:08:40,061 --> 00:08:41,980
Welcome onboard.

140
00:08:42,063 --> 00:08:44,858
But if there's no atmosphere out there,
what's that?

141
00:08:44,941 --> 00:08:48,278
IDA: Stars breaking up. Gas clouds.

142
00:08:48,695 --> 00:08:53,575
We have whole solar systems
being ripped apart above our heads,

143
00:08:54,117 --> 00:08:55,910
before falling into that thing.

144
00:08:55,994 --> 00:08:57,954
So, a bit worse than a storm, then.

145
00:08:58,121 --> 00:09:00,248
-Just a bit.
-Just a bit, yeah.

146
00:09:18,016 --> 00:09:19,768
VOICE: (WHISPERING) Toby.

147
00:09:27,275 --> 00:09:29,027
Who's that?

148
00:09:33,323 --> 00:09:34,991
Danny?

149
00:09:41,414 --> 00:09:44,292
-Close door 1.
-The rocket link's fine.

150
00:09:47,837 --> 00:09:52,634
That's the black hole,
officially designated K37 Gem 5.

151
00:09:52,717 --> 00:09:55,553
In the scriptures of the Veltino,

152
00:09:55,637 --> 00:09:59,974
this planet is called Krop Tor, the bitter pill.

153
00:10:00,058 --> 00:10:04,145
And the black hole
is supposed to be a mighty demon

154
00:10:04,229 --> 00:10:07,190
who was tricked into devouring the planet

155
00:10:07,357 --> 00:10:10,902
only to spit it out because it was poison.

156
00:10:11,945 --> 00:10:15,740
-The bitter pill. I like that.
-We are so far out.

157
00:10:15,824 --> 00:10:19,285
Lost in the drifts of the universe.
How did you even get here?

158
00:10:19,369 --> 00:10:21,538
We flew in. You see...

159
00:10:22,747 --> 00:10:25,625
this planet's generating a gravity field.

160
00:10:25,708 --> 00:10:28,044
We don't know how, we've no idea,

161
00:10:28,128 --> 00:10:32,132
but it's kept in constant balance
against the black hole.

162
00:10:32,215 --> 00:10:36,469
And the field extends out there as a funnel,

163
00:10:36,553 --> 00:10:41,641
a distinct gravity funnel
reaching out into clear space.

164
00:10:41,724 --> 00:10:43,184
That was our way in.

165
00:10:43,268 --> 00:10:46,563
You flew down that thing?
Like a roller coaster.

166
00:10:46,646 --> 00:10:49,482
By rights,
the ship should've been torn apart.

167
00:10:49,566 --> 00:10:52,652
We lost the captain,
which is what put me in charge.

168
00:10:52,735 --> 00:10:54,487
And you're doing a good job.

169
00:10:54,571 --> 00:10:56,573
Yeah, well. Needs must.

170
00:10:57,240 --> 00:11:00,535
But if that gravity funnel closes,
there's no way out.

171
00:11:00,618 --> 00:11:02,620
Oh, we have fun speculating about that.

172
00:11:02,745 --> 00:11:05,373
Oh, yeah. That's the word, "fun".

173
00:11:05,456 --> 00:11:09,085
But that field would take
phenomenal amounts of power, I mean...

174
00:11:09,794 --> 00:11:13,173
Not just big, but off the scale. Can I...?

175
00:11:14,007 --> 00:11:16,259
Sure, help yourself.

176
00:11:19,012 --> 00:11:20,430
Your refreshment.

177
00:11:20,513 --> 00:11:22,473
Oh, yeah, thanks. Thank you.

178
00:11:22,599 --> 00:11:24,767
I'm sorry, what was your name?

179
00:11:24,893 --> 00:11:28,313
We have no titles. We are as one.

180
00:11:29,772 --> 00:11:32,025
Erm, what are they called?

181
00:11:32,650 --> 00:11:36,112
Oh, come on. Where have you been living?
Everyone's got one.

182
00:11:36,237 --> 00:11:38,406
Well, not me. So, what are they?

183
00:11:39,032 --> 00:11:41,284
-They're the Ood.
-The Ood?

184
00:11:41,367 --> 00:11:43,203
The Ood.

185
00:11:43,286 --> 00:11:45,163
Well, that's Ood.

186
00:11:45,288 --> 00:11:47,582
Very Ood. But handy.

187
00:11:47,665 --> 00:11:50,335
They work the mine shaft,
all the drilling and stuff.

188
00:11:50,418 --> 00:11:52,170
Supervision and maintenance.

189
00:11:52,253 --> 00:11:55,340
They're born for it. Basic slave race.

190
00:11:55,757 --> 00:11:57,091
You've got slaves?

191
00:11:57,175 --> 00:11:59,802
Don't start. She's like one of that lot,
Friends of the Ood.

192
00:11:59,928 --> 00:12:02,972
Well, maybe I am, yeah.
Since when do humans need slaves?

193
00:12:03,097 --> 00:12:05,266
But the Ood offer themselves.

194
00:12:05,391 --> 00:12:08,770
If you don't give them orders,
they just pine away and die.

195
00:12:09,646 --> 00:12:12,357
Seriously? You like being ordered about?

196
00:12:13,149 --> 00:12:14,859
It is all we crave.

197
00:12:14,943 --> 00:12:18,279
-Why is that, then?
-We have nothing else in life.

198
00:12:18,363 --> 00:12:21,199
Yeah, well, I used to think like that.

199
00:12:21,324 --> 00:12:23,826
-Long time ago.
-DOCTOR: There we go. Do you see?

200
00:12:23,910 --> 00:12:25,828
To generate that gravity field
and the funnel,

201
00:12:25,912 --> 00:12:28,414
you'd need a power source
with an inverted self-extrapolating reflex

202
00:12:28,498 --> 00:12:30,667
of six to the power of six every six seconds.

203
00:12:30,750 --> 00:12:32,669
-That's all the sixes.
-And it's impossible.

204
00:12:32,752 --> 00:12:34,754
It took us two years to work that out.

205
00:12:34,837 --> 00:12:38,633
-I'm very good.
-But that's why we're here.

206
00:12:39,175 --> 00:12:43,054
This power source is ten miles below,
through solid rock.

207
00:12:43,179 --> 00:12:45,848
Point 0.
We're drilling down to try and find it.

208
00:12:45,932 --> 00:12:49,185
It's giving off readings
of over 90 Statts on the Blazen Scale.

209
00:12:49,269 --> 00:12:51,187
It could revolutionise modern science.

210
00:12:51,312 --> 00:12:53,648
We could use it to fuel the empire.

211
00:12:53,731 --> 00:12:55,108
Or start a war.

212
00:12:55,191 --> 00:12:59,028
It's buried beneath us.
In the darkness, waiting.

213
00:12:59,112 --> 00:13:01,698
What's your job? Chief dramatist?

214
00:13:02,490 --> 00:13:06,035
Well, whatever it is down there,
it's not a natural phenomenon.

215
00:13:06,119 --> 00:13:08,496
This planet once supported life,

216
00:13:08,579 --> 00:13:11,291
aeons ago, before the human race
had even learnt to walk.

217
00:13:11,374 --> 00:13:13,751
I saw that lettering written on the wall,
did you do that?

218
00:13:13,876 --> 00:13:16,296
I copied it from fragments
we found unearthed by the drilling,

219
00:13:16,379 --> 00:13:18,298
but I can't translate it.

220
00:13:18,381 --> 00:13:21,050
No, neither can I.
And that's saying something.

221
00:13:21,175 --> 00:13:24,304
And there was some form of civilisation.

222
00:13:24,429 --> 00:13:26,431
They buried something.

223
00:13:26,556 --> 00:13:28,683
Now, it's reaching out.

224
00:13:28,766 --> 00:13:30,768
Calling us in.

225
00:13:30,852 --> 00:13:32,645
And you came.

226
00:13:32,729 --> 00:13:34,981
How could we not?

227
00:13:35,064 --> 00:13:38,484
So, when it comes right down to it,
why did you come here?

228
00:13:38,568 --> 00:13:41,571
Why did you do that? Why? I'll tell you why.

229
00:13:42,405 --> 00:13:44,907
Because it was there. Brilliant!

230
00:13:45,408 --> 00:13:48,202
-Excuse me. Zack, wasn't it?
-That's me.

231
00:13:48,369 --> 00:13:52,165
Just stand there 'cause I'm gonna hug you,
is that all right?

232
00:13:52,248 --> 00:13:53,708
Suppose so.

233
00:13:53,833 --> 00:13:55,710
Here we go. Coming in.

234
00:13:58,463 --> 00:14:02,091
Human beings. You are amazing.

235
00:14:05,053 --> 00:14:07,430
-DOCTOR: Thank you.
-Not at all.

236
00:14:07,930 --> 00:14:10,099
But apart from that,
you're completely mad.

237
00:14:10,183 --> 00:14:12,685
You should pack your bags,
get back on that ship and fly for your lives.

238
00:14:12,769 --> 00:14:15,396
You can talk. How the hell did you get here?

239
00:14:15,480 --> 00:14:20,902
Oh, I've got this... This ship...
It's hard to explain, it just sort of appears.

240
00:14:20,985 --> 00:14:24,238
We can show you,
we parked down the corridor from...

241
00:14:24,322 --> 00:14:27,367
-What's it called? Habitation Area 37
-3.

242
00:14:28,326 --> 00:14:30,495
Do you mean Storage 67

243
00:14:30,578 --> 00:14:33,039
It was a bit of a cupboard, yeah.

244
00:14:33,122 --> 00:14:35,541
Storage 67 But you said...

245
00:14:35,625 --> 00:14:37,418
You said...

246
00:14:37,960 --> 00:14:40,046
You said Storage 5 to 8.

247
00:14:44,384 --> 00:14:45,885
What is it? What's wrong?

248
00:14:45,968 --> 00:14:47,804
Open door 189.

249
00:14:49,305 --> 00:14:50,973
Close door 18.

250
00:14:52,934 --> 00:14:55,978
-Doors, come on!
-Open door 17.

251
00:14:57,688 --> 00:14:59,315
Open door 15.

252
00:15:00,983 --> 00:15:03,694
-Open door 16.
-It can't be, it can't be!

253
00:15:03,820 --> 00:15:06,239
What's wrong? What is it?

254
00:15:06,364 --> 00:15:09,158
Doctor, the Tardis is in there.
What's happened?

255
00:15:10,410 --> 00:15:12,120
The Tardis is gone.

256
00:15:12,328 --> 00:15:14,831
Door 16 out of commission.

257
00:15:17,500 --> 00:15:21,003
The earthquake. This section collapsed.

258
00:15:22,004 --> 00:15:24,549
But it's got to be out there somewhere.

259
00:15:26,843 --> 00:15:28,511
Look down.

260
00:15:35,309 --> 00:15:39,147
The ground gave way. My Tardis must have
fallen down into the heart of the planet.

261
00:15:39,230 --> 00:15:41,274
You've got robot drills
heading the same way.

262
00:15:41,357 --> 00:15:43,526
We can't divert the drilling.

263
00:15:45,987 --> 00:15:49,699
But I need my ship!
It's all I've got. Literally, the only thing.

264
00:15:49,782 --> 00:15:52,952
Doctor, we've only got the resources
to dig one central shaft

265
00:15:53,035 --> 00:15:55,288
down to the power source and that's it.

266
00:15:55,371 --> 00:15:59,125
No diversions, no distractions,
no exceptions.

267
00:16:00,751 --> 00:16:02,879
Your machine is lost.

268
00:16:03,004 --> 00:16:05,923
Alll can do is offer you a lift,
if we ever get to leave this place.

269
00:16:06,007 --> 00:16:08,551
And that is the end of it.

270
00:16:10,970 --> 00:16:13,764
I'll put you on the duty roster.

271
00:16:14,223 --> 00:16:16,476
We need someone in the laundry.

272
00:16:18,936 --> 00:16:20,563
Open door 1.

273
00:16:23,858 --> 00:16:25,443
Close door 1.

274
00:16:31,115 --> 00:16:34,327
-I've trapped you here.
-No, don't worry about me.

275
00:16:34,410 --> 00:16:36,245
(RUMBLING)

276
00:16:38,164 --> 00:16:40,917
Okay, we're on a planet
that shouldn't exist,

277
00:16:41,000 --> 00:16:43,586
underneath a black hole

278
00:16:43,711 --> 00:16:45,296
and no way out.

279
00:16:47,048 --> 00:16:50,551
Yeah, I've changed my mind.
Start worrying about me.

280
00:17:02,355 --> 00:17:03,856
COMPUTER: Entering night shift.

281
00:17:03,940 --> 00:17:08,486
Your chosen track for transition
ls Ravel's Bolero.

282
00:17:08,569 --> 00:17:10,780
(BOLERO PLAYING ON PA)

283
00:17:39,559 --> 00:17:42,228
All finished. Heading back inside.

284
00:17:47,984 --> 00:17:49,819
Server Gamma 10.

285
00:17:51,612 --> 00:17:53,489
Server Gamma 11.

286
00:17:54,657 --> 00:17:56,284
Server Gamma 12.

287
00:18:06,168 --> 00:18:08,254
(PA CUTS OUT ABRUPTLY)

288
00:18:11,340 --> 00:18:13,092
VOICE: (WHISPERING) Toby.

289
00:18:18,514 --> 00:18:21,100
-I can see you.
-Danny, is that you?

290
00:18:22,560 --> 00:18:24,770
It's not funny, all right?

291
00:18:26,522 --> 00:18:27,565
Dan?

292
00:18:31,485 --> 00:18:33,446
I'm trying to work, Daniel.

293
00:18:36,574 --> 00:18:39,493
(STUTTERING) If that's you, Dan,
can you just stop it?

294
00:18:39,577 --> 00:18:41,871
(BUZZING)

295
00:18:53,966 --> 00:18:57,386
ZACK: (ON PA) Danny,
check the temperature in Ood Habitation.

296
00:18:57,470 --> 00:18:59,430
It seems to be rising.

297
00:19:03,309 --> 00:19:06,020
Help yourself, just don't have the green.

298
00:19:06,103 --> 00:19:07,855
Or the blue.

299
00:19:12,193 --> 00:19:13,986
Um, a bit of that, thanks.

300
00:19:16,155 --> 00:19:18,282
Would you like sauce with that?

301
00:19:18,366 --> 00:19:20,201
I'll have a go, yeah.

302
00:19:24,413 --> 00:19:28,250
I did that job once. I was a dinner lady.

303
00:19:28,376 --> 00:19:30,461
Not that I'm calling you a lady.

304
00:19:31,796 --> 00:19:34,090
Although, I don't know, you might be.

305
00:19:35,174 --> 00:19:38,427
Do you actually get paid, though?
Do they give you money?

306
00:19:38,511 --> 00:19:43,140
The Beast and his armies shall rise
from the Pit to make war against God.

307
00:19:45,059 --> 00:19:46,519
I'm sorry?

308
00:19:47,895 --> 00:19:51,649
Apologies.
I said I hope you enjoy your meal.

309
00:19:52,692 --> 00:19:53,859
Yeah.

310
00:19:59,615 --> 00:20:02,201
COMPUTER: Drill head now at point 16.

311
00:20:04,120 --> 00:20:06,247
Drill head speed increasing.

312
00:20:06,330 --> 00:20:08,165
Keep pressure at 60.

313
00:20:13,379 --> 00:20:14,964
(GROWLING)

314
00:20:24,765 --> 00:20:26,225
Close door 3.

315
00:20:26,308 --> 00:20:28,394
(MOCKING) Close door 3.

316
00:20:28,477 --> 00:20:30,271
He is awake.

317
00:20:31,814 --> 00:20:33,274
What did you say?

318
00:20:33,357 --> 00:20:34,900
Close door 3.

319
00:20:46,078 --> 00:20:48,289
VOICE: (WHISPERING) Toby.

320
00:20:51,250 --> 00:20:53,627
Don't turn around.

321
00:20:56,088 --> 00:20:57,256
Dan?

322
00:21:00,509 --> 00:21:03,137
-That's not Dan.
-Don't look at me.

323
00:21:04,221 --> 00:21:05,681
(STUTTERING) Who are you?

324
00:21:05,765 --> 00:21:08,517
I have so many names.

325
00:21:09,143 --> 00:21:10,644
If I could...

326
00:21:10,728 --> 00:21:13,189
If you look at me, you will die.

327
00:21:13,272 --> 00:21:15,566
But who are you?

328
00:21:15,649 --> 00:21:18,068
I'm behind you, Toby.

329
00:21:18,152 --> 00:21:20,654
I'm right behind you.

330
00:21:20,738 --> 00:21:24,074
Don't look. Don't look at me.

331
00:21:26,452 --> 00:21:28,788
One look and you will die.

332
00:21:30,122 --> 00:21:32,541
I'm reaching out, Toby.

333
00:21:32,958 --> 00:21:35,211
I'm so close.

334
00:21:35,336 --> 00:21:37,671
Don't turn around.

335
00:21:38,422 --> 00:21:42,301
Oh, I can touch you.

336
00:22:17,586 --> 00:22:18,921
No.

337
00:22:37,940 --> 00:22:40,401
Zack, we got a problem?

338
00:22:40,484 --> 00:22:42,611
ZACK: No more than usual.

339
00:22:42,695 --> 00:22:45,447
Got the Scarlet System burning up.
Might be worth a look.

340
00:22:45,531 --> 00:22:48,659
You might want to see this.
Moment in history.

341
00:22:58,836 --> 00:23:01,547
There, on the edge.

342
00:23:02,840 --> 00:23:04,633
That red cloud.

343
00:23:05,718 --> 00:23:09,471
That used to be the Scarlet System.

344
00:23:10,472 --> 00:23:12,141
Home to the Pallushi.

345
00:23:13,017 --> 00:23:17,104
A mighty civilisation
spanning a billion years

346
00:23:17,187 --> 00:23:19,982
disappearing forever.

347
00:23:21,692 --> 00:23:24,320
Their planets and suns consumed.

348
00:23:26,739 --> 00:23:31,535
Ladies and gentlemen,
we have witnessed its passing.

349
00:23:32,828 --> 00:23:34,705
No, could you leave it open?

350
00:23:35,414 --> 00:23:38,417
Just for a bit. I won't go mad, I promise.

351
00:23:38,500 --> 00:23:40,502
How would you know?

352
00:23:41,378 --> 00:23:43,756
Scooti, check the lockdown.

353
00:23:43,839 --> 00:23:46,800
Jefferson, sign off the airlock seals for me.

354
00:23:46,884 --> 00:23:48,510
Open door 18.

355
00:23:48,636 --> 00:23:50,888
I've seen films and things, yeah?

356
00:23:51,013 --> 00:23:54,224
They say black holes are like
gateways to another universe.

357
00:23:54,350 --> 00:23:55,601
Close door 18.

358
00:23:55,684 --> 00:23:58,771
Not that one. It just eats.

359
00:24:00,230 --> 00:24:02,316
A long way from home.

360
00:24:05,152 --> 00:24:06,654
Go that way,

361
00:24:06,737 --> 00:24:10,074
turn right, keep going for, erm...

362
00:24:10,157 --> 00:24:14,536
about 500 years and you'll reach the Earth.

363
00:24:18,958 --> 00:24:20,459
No signal.

364
00:24:20,542 --> 00:24:22,628
That's first time we've gone out of range.

365
00:24:22,711 --> 00:24:25,005
Mind you, even if I could...

366
00:24:26,548 --> 00:24:28,592
What would I tell her?

367
00:24:31,512 --> 00:24:33,889
Can you build another Tardis?

368
00:24:35,516 --> 00:24:37,851
They were grown, not built.

369
00:24:37,935 --> 00:24:41,230
And with my home planet gone,

370
00:24:41,313 --> 00:24:42,898
we're kind of stuck.

371
00:24:44,066 --> 00:24:47,486
Well, it could be worse.
This lot said they'd give us a lift.

372
00:24:47,569 --> 00:24:49,279
And then what?

373
00:24:50,239 --> 00:24:52,574
I don't know.

374
00:24:52,658 --> 00:24:54,994
Find a planet. Get a job.

375
00:24:55,077 --> 00:24:58,205
You live your life
same as the rest of the universe.

376
00:24:58,288 --> 00:25:00,499
I'd have to settle down.

377
00:25:01,250 --> 00:25:04,920
Get a house or something.
A proper house with...

378
00:25:05,045 --> 00:25:08,424
doors and things. Carpets.
Me, living in a house!

379
00:25:08,549 --> 00:25:11,677
Now, that... That... That is terrifying.

380
00:25:11,760 --> 00:25:13,721
You'd have to get a mortgage.

381
00:25:13,804 --> 00:25:15,180
-No.
-Oh, yes.

382
00:25:15,264 --> 00:25:17,641
I'm dying. That's it, I am dying.
It is all over.

383
00:25:17,725 --> 00:25:19,977
What about me? I'd have to get one, too.

384
00:25:20,102 --> 00:25:23,605
I don't know, could be the same one.
We could both...

385
00:25:25,441 --> 00:25:27,693
I don't know, share.

386
00:25:27,776 --> 00:25:30,988
Or not. Whatever.
I don't know. All sorts of...

387
00:25:31,113 --> 00:25:33,157
-Anyway...
-We'll see.

388
00:25:37,202 --> 00:25:40,289
I promised Jackie
I would always take you back home.

389
00:25:42,124 --> 00:25:44,251
Everyone leaves home in the end.

390
00:25:45,961 --> 00:25:47,880
Not to end up stuck here.

391
00:25:47,963 --> 00:25:50,716
Yeah, but stuck with you, that's not so bad.

392
00:25:52,634 --> 00:25:54,136
-Yeah?
-Yes.

393
00:25:55,054 --> 00:25:57,264
(MOBILE RINGING)

394
00:26:01,560 --> 00:26:03,771
VOICE: He is awake.

395
00:26:10,986 --> 00:26:13,489
-DOCTOR: Evening.
-Only us.

396
00:26:13,614 --> 00:26:16,742
The mysterious couple.
How are you, then? Settling in?

397
00:26:16,825 --> 00:26:21,246
Yeah, sorry, straight to business.
The Ood, how do they communicate?

398
00:26:21,330 --> 00:26:22,664
I mean, with each other?

399
00:26:22,748 --> 00:26:24,958
Oh, just empaths.

400
00:26:25,042 --> 00:26:28,170
There's a low-level telepathic field
connecting them.

401
00:26:28,295 --> 00:26:32,800
Not that that does them much good.
They're basically a herd race, like cattle.

402
00:26:32,883 --> 00:26:35,552
This telepathic field,
can it pick up messages?

403
00:26:35,677 --> 00:26:39,640
'Cause I was having dinner
and one of the Oods said something...

404
00:26:39,723 --> 00:26:41,433
Well, odd.

405
00:26:41,517 --> 00:26:43,268
Hmm. An odd Ood.

406
00:26:43,352 --> 00:26:46,480
And then I got something else on my...

407
00:26:46,563 --> 00:26:47,981
communicator thing.

408
00:26:48,065 --> 00:26:49,942
Well, be fair.

409
00:26:50,025 --> 00:26:53,362
We've got whole star systems
burning up around us,

410
00:26:53,445 --> 00:26:56,365
there's all sorts of stray transmissions.

411
00:26:56,448 --> 00:26:58,534
Probably nothing.

412
00:26:58,617 --> 00:27:02,204
Look, if there was something wrong,
it would show.

413
00:27:02,329 --> 00:27:04,873
We monitor the telepathic field.

414
00:27:04,998 --> 00:27:06,959
It's the only way to look after them.

415
00:27:07,042 --> 00:27:10,921
They're so stupid.
They don't even tell us when they're ill.

416
00:27:11,004 --> 00:27:14,133
-Monitor the field, that's this thing.
-Yeah.

417
00:27:14,216 --> 00:27:18,720
But like I said, it's low-level telepathy.
They only register Basic 5.

418
00:27:19,263 --> 00:27:21,431
Well, that's not Basic 5. 10.

419
00:27:22,933 --> 00:27:24,184
20.

420
00:27:25,477 --> 00:27:28,313
-They've gone up to Basic 30.
-But they can't.

421
00:27:28,397 --> 00:27:30,107
Doctor, the Ood.

422
00:27:32,568 --> 00:27:34,903
What does Basic 30 mean?

423
00:27:34,987 --> 00:27:39,533
Well, it means that they're shouting,
screaming inside their heads.

424
00:27:39,616 --> 00:27:41,702
Or something is shouting at them.

425
00:27:41,785 --> 00:27:45,581
But where is it coming from?
What is it saying?

426
00:27:45,789 --> 00:27:47,541
What did it say to you?

427
00:27:47,624 --> 00:27:50,002
Something about the Beast and the Pit.

428
00:27:50,169 --> 00:27:53,046
What about your communicator?
What did that say?

429
00:27:55,465 --> 00:27:56,884
He is awake.

430
00:27:56,967 --> 00:27:59,511
THE OOD: And you will worship him.

431
00:27:59,595 --> 00:28:02,723
-What the hell?
-He is awake.

432
00:28:02,931 --> 00:28:05,100
THE OOD: And you will worship him.

433
00:28:05,267 --> 00:28:06,602
Worship who?

434
00:28:08,187 --> 00:28:11,481
Who's talking to you? Who is it?

435
00:28:12,232 --> 00:28:14,651
Toby, I've got your expenditure.

436
00:28:15,777 --> 00:28:17,779
Open door 41.

437
00:28:19,072 --> 00:28:20,866
Close door 41.

438
00:28:23,994 --> 00:28:25,454
417

439
00:28:26,788 --> 00:28:28,457
Close door 40.

440
00:28:29,958 --> 00:28:32,085
Computer, did you open and close door 417

441
00:28:32,169 --> 00:28:33,378
Confirmed.

442
00:28:33,462 --> 00:28:36,506
But that's the airlock.
Why would you open the airlock?

443
00:28:36,590 --> 00:28:39,009
It's the night shift,
we're not allowed outside.

444
00:28:39,092 --> 00:28:41,887
-Has someone gone out?
-Confirmed.

445
00:28:41,970 --> 00:28:44,514
-But who was it?
-Cannot confirm.

446
00:28:46,141 --> 00:28:48,101
Okay. Right, hold on, I know.

447
00:28:48,227 --> 00:28:50,479
Tell me whose spacesuit
has been logged out.

448
00:28:50,562 --> 00:28:53,565
-No spacesuit has been logged out.
-But...

449
00:28:54,149 --> 00:28:57,986
You're not making any sense.
You can't go outside without...

450
00:28:58,070 --> 00:29:00,197
Zack, I think we've got a breakdown
on door 41.

451
00:29:00,280 --> 00:29:02,908
It's saying somebody's gone outside
onto the planet's surface.

452
00:29:02,991 --> 00:29:04,159
(STATIC)

453
00:29:04,243 --> 00:29:05,410
Zack?

454
00:29:06,119 --> 00:29:07,204
Zack?

455
00:29:08,997 --> 00:29:11,833
-Computer, trace fault.
-There is no fault.

456
00:29:11,959 --> 00:29:15,754
-Tell me who went through that door?
-He is awake.

457
00:29:16,630 --> 00:29:18,840
-What?
-He ls awake.

458
00:29:20,467 --> 00:29:24,012
-What's that supposed to mean?
-He bathes in the black sun.

459
00:29:48,495 --> 00:29:49,621
Toby.

460
00:29:50,747 --> 00:29:52,916
There's no air, there's no...

461
00:30:16,231 --> 00:30:18,942
No, stop it! You can't be!

462
00:30:25,657 --> 00:30:28,994
Open door 40! Open door 40!

463
00:30:29,578 --> 00:30:33,040
Open door 40! Open door 40!

464
00:30:33,749 --> 00:30:35,125
Open door 40!

465
00:30:35,625 --> 00:30:36,835
(SCREAMING)

466
00:30:41,715 --> 00:30:45,510
Emergency hull breach.
Emergency hull breach.

467
00:30:45,594 --> 00:30:47,095
Which section?

468
00:30:47,220 --> 00:30:51,350
Everyone, evacuate 11 to 13.
We've got a breach.

469
00:30:51,433 --> 00:30:55,103
The Base is open. Repeat, the Base is open.

470
00:31:00,275 --> 00:31:02,110
Open door 189.

471
00:31:04,905 --> 00:31:06,448
Close door 18.

472
00:31:06,531 --> 00:31:10,077
I can't contain the oxygen field.
We're gonna lose it.

473
00:31:10,160 --> 00:31:13,789
Come on! Keep moving!

474
00:31:15,791 --> 00:31:18,543
And you, too, sunshine!

475
00:31:20,295 --> 00:31:22,130
-Everyone all right?
-Breach sealed.

476
00:31:22,255 --> 00:31:25,425
-What happened? What was it?
-Hull breach.

477
00:31:25,509 --> 00:31:27,761
We were open to the elements.
Another couple of minutes

478
00:31:27,886 --> 00:31:30,430
and we'd have been inspecting
that black hole at close quarters.

479
00:31:30,514 --> 00:31:32,224
That wasn't a quake. What caused it?

480
00:31:32,307 --> 00:31:36,645
We've lost sections 11 to 13.
Everyone all right?

481
00:31:36,728 --> 00:31:39,439
We've got everyone here except Scooti.

482
00:31:39,523 --> 00:31:41,400
Scooti, report.

483
00:31:42,651 --> 00:31:45,612
Scooti Manista, this is an order, report.

484
00:31:46,279 --> 00:31:47,906
ZACK: She"s all right.

485
00:31:47,989 --> 00:31:50,659
I've picked up her bio chip.
She's in Habitation 3.

486
00:31:50,784 --> 00:31:52,744
Better go and check
if she's not responding.

487
00:31:52,828 --> 00:31:54,621
She might be unconscious.

488
00:31:54,746 --> 00:31:57,707
ZACK: But how about that eh? We survived.

489
00:31:57,791 --> 00:31:59,751
Habitation 3. Come on.

490
00:31:59,835 --> 00:32:03,130
I don't often say this,
but I think we could all do with a drink.

491
00:32:03,213 --> 00:32:04,798
Come on.

492
00:32:06,383 --> 00:32:07,843
What happened?

493
00:32:07,968 --> 00:32:11,096
(STUTTERING) I don't know.
I was working and then I can't remember.

494
00:32:11,179 --> 00:32:14,266
All that noise. The room was falling apart.
There was no air.

495
00:32:14,349 --> 00:32:17,936
Come on, up you get.
Come and have some Protein One.

496
00:32:18,019 --> 00:32:20,564
-You've gone native.
-0i, don't knock it, it's nice.

497
00:32:20,647 --> 00:32:23,400
Protein One with just a dash of Three.

498
00:32:24,693 --> 00:32:27,487
There's no sign of her,
but the bio chip says she's in this area.

499
00:32:27,571 --> 00:32:31,116
IDA: Scooti, please respond.
If you can hear this, please respond.

500
00:32:31,199 --> 00:32:34,411
-Habitation 6...
-Nowhere here.

501
00:32:34,494 --> 00:32:37,289
Zack, we've got a problem.
Scooti's still missing.

502
00:32:37,372 --> 00:32:39,040
ZACK: But it says Habitation 3.

503
00:32:39,124 --> 00:32:41,751
Well, that's where I am
and I'm telling you, she's not here.

504
00:32:41,835 --> 00:32:43,712
I've found her.

505
00:32:44,463 --> 00:32:45,714
Oh, my God.

506
00:32:52,262 --> 00:32:54,222
Sorry. I'm so sorry.

507
00:33:01,021 --> 00:33:02,147
Captain...

508
00:33:03,815 --> 00:33:07,569
report Officer Scootori Manista, PKD...

509
00:33:09,738 --> 00:33:11,364
deceased.

510
00:33:12,657 --> 00:33:14,242
43K 2.1.

511
00:33:17,621 --> 00:33:19,164
She was 20.

512
00:33:20,957 --> 00:33:22,542
20 years old.

513
00:33:39,017 --> 00:33:41,436
For how should man die better

514
00:33:42,270 --> 00:33:44,356
Than facing fearful odds

515
00:33:45,607 --> 00:33:47,776
For the ashes of his father

516
00:33:49,945 --> 00:33:53,949
And the temples of his gods?

517
00:33:58,787 --> 00:34:00,789
(RUMBLING STOPS)

518
00:34:00,872 --> 00:34:02,582
It's stopped.

519
00:34:04,000 --> 00:34:05,961
What was that?

520
00:34:06,086 --> 00:34:08,463
-What was it?
-The drill.

521
00:34:10,048 --> 00:34:12,801
We've stopped drilling. We've made it.

522
00:34:14,052 --> 00:34:15,136
Point 0.

523
00:34:15,929 --> 00:34:18,974
ZACK: All non-essential Oods
to be confined.

524
00:34:19,808 --> 00:34:23,603
Capsule established.
All systems functioning.

525
00:34:23,687 --> 00:34:27,732
The mine shaft is go.
Bring systems online now.

526
00:34:27,816 --> 00:34:30,235
Reporting as a volunteer
for the expeditionary force.

527
00:34:30,318 --> 00:34:34,239
Doctor, this is breaking
every single protocol.

528
00:34:34,322 --> 00:34:39,202
-We don't even know who you are.
-Yeah, but you trust me, don't you?

529
00:34:39,327 --> 00:34:41,955
And you can't let Ida
go down there on her own.

530
00:34:42,038 --> 00:34:46,626
Go on, look me in the eye.
Yes, you do. I can see it. Trust.

531
00:34:47,544 --> 00:34:49,337
I should be going down.

532
00:34:50,005 --> 00:34:53,883
The captain doesn't lead the mission.
He stays here, in charge.

533
00:34:54,009 --> 00:34:56,136
Not much good here, am I?

534
00:34:59,598 --> 00:35:00,849
Positions!

535
00:35:00,932 --> 00:35:04,644
We're going down in two!
Everyone, positions!

536
00:35:04,728 --> 00:35:07,606
Mr Jefferson, I want maximum systems...

537
00:35:07,689 --> 00:35:11,526
Oxygen, nitro balance, gravity.
It's ages since I wore one of these.

538
00:35:11,610 --> 00:35:14,446
I want that spacesuit back in one piece.
You got that?

539
00:35:14,529 --> 00:35:16,031
Yes, sir.

540
00:35:17,240 --> 00:35:22,454
It's funny 'cause people back home
think that space travel is gonna be all...

541
00:35:22,537 --> 00:35:27,584
whizzing about and teleports, anti-gravity.

542
00:35:28,752 --> 00:35:30,879
But it's not, is it? It's tough.

543
00:35:31,546 --> 00:35:33,381
I'll see you later.

544
00:35:34,049 --> 00:35:35,884
Not if I see you first.

545
00:35:44,100 --> 00:35:48,855
You will remain here.
No command can override this.

546
00:35:49,689 --> 00:35:51,608
Have you got that?

547
00:35:52,734 --> 00:35:54,819
My instructions only.

548
00:35:59,407 --> 00:36:00,909
Capsule active.

549
00:36:02,243 --> 00:36:06,206
Counting down, in ten, nine,

550
00:36:06,289 --> 00:36:11,252
eight, seven, six, five,

551
00:36:11,628 --> 00:36:15,298
four, three, two,

552
00:36:15,757 --> 00:36:18,134
one, release.

553
00:37:01,553 --> 00:37:04,889
You've gone beyond the oxygen field.
You're on your own.

554
00:37:14,149 --> 00:37:17,152
Don't forget to breathe. Breathing is good.

555
00:37:18,278 --> 00:37:20,989
-Rose, stay off the comm.
-No chance.

556
00:37:49,225 --> 00:37:51,311
(ALARM BLARING)

557
00:37:53,563 --> 00:37:56,649
Doctor? Doctor, are you all right?

558
00:37:56,733 --> 00:37:59,277
Ida, report to me.

559
00:37:59,360 --> 00:38:00,862
Doctor?

560
00:38:01,488 --> 00:38:05,533
DOCTOR: It's all right. We've made it.
Heading out of the capsule now.

561
00:38:10,955 --> 00:38:13,041
ROSE: What's it like down there?

562
00:38:13,124 --> 00:38:14,709
It's hard to tell.

563
00:38:15,877 --> 00:38:20,340
Some sort of cave. Cavern. It's massive.

564
00:38:20,423 --> 00:38:23,593
Well, this should help. Gravity globe.

565
00:38:33,728 --> 00:38:35,063
That's...

566
00:38:35,730 --> 00:38:37,065
That's...

567
00:38:38,066 --> 00:38:40,944
Oh, my God. That's beautiful.

568
00:38:42,070 --> 00:38:44,197
Rose...

569
00:38:44,280 --> 00:38:46,491
you can tell Toby...

570
00:38:48,034 --> 00:38:50,370
we've found his civilisation.

571
00:38:52,914 --> 00:38:55,792
Oi, Toby, sounds like
you've got plenty of work.

572
00:38:55,917 --> 00:38:57,585
Good, good.

573
00:38:58,253 --> 00:38:59,462
Good.

574
00:38:59,587 --> 00:39:02,507
Concentrate now, people.
Keep on the mission.

575
00:39:03,049 --> 00:39:05,927
Ida, what about the power source?

576
00:39:06,427 --> 00:39:08,179
We're close.

577
00:39:08,263 --> 00:39:11,850
Energy signature indicates north-northwest.

578
00:39:11,933 --> 00:39:13,977
Are you getting pictures up there?

579
00:39:14,102 --> 00:39:17,313
ZACK: There's too much interference.
We're in your hands.

580
00:39:17,438 --> 00:39:21,401
Well, we've come this far.
There's no turning back.

581
00:39:21,484 --> 00:39:23,528
DOCTOR: Oh, did you have to?

582
00:39:23,611 --> 00:39:27,949
No turning back? That's almost as bad as,
"Nothing can possibly go wrong"

583
00:39:28,032 --> 00:39:30,702
or "This is gonna be the best Christmas
Walford's ever had."”

584
00:39:30,785 --> 00:39:32,912
Have you finished?

585
00:39:34,914 --> 00:39:36,749
Yeah. Finished.

586
00:39:44,674 --> 00:39:48,720
Captain, sir, there's something happening
with the Ood.

587
00:39:49,220 --> 00:39:51,139
What are they doing?

588
00:39:51,472 --> 00:39:52,974
They're staring at me.

589
00:39:53,057 --> 00:39:55,643
I've told them to stop, but they won't.

590
00:39:56,644 --> 00:40:00,106
Danny, you're a big boy,
I think you can take being stared at.

591
00:40:00,648 --> 00:40:04,819
But the telepathic field, sir,
it's at Basic 100.

592
00:40:05,486 --> 00:40:08,781
I've checked. There isn't any fault.

593
00:40:08,865 --> 00:40:11,910
-It's definitely 100.
-ZACK: But that's impossible.

594
00:40:11,993 --> 00:40:14,579
-What's Basic 100 mean?
-They should be dead.

595
00:40:14,662 --> 00:40:16,748
Basic 100 is brain death.

596
00:40:16,831 --> 00:40:19,417
But they're safe?
They're not actually moving?

597
00:40:19,500 --> 00:40:20,585
No, sir.

598
00:40:20,668 --> 00:40:26,007
Keep watching them. And you, Jefferson,
keep a guard on the Ood.

599
00:40:26,090 --> 00:40:27,759
Officer at arms.

600
00:40:27,842 --> 00:40:30,178
You can't fire a gun in here.
What if you hit a wall?

601
00:40:30,261 --> 00:40:33,932
Firing Stock 15,
only impacts upon organics.

602
00:40:34,015 --> 00:40:36,100
-Keep watch. Guard them.
-Yes, sir.

603
00:40:36,184 --> 00:40:38,937
-DOCTOR: Is everything all right up there?
-Yeah, yeah.

604
00:40:39,020 --> 00:40:40,688
-It's fine.
-Great.

605
00:40:45,193 --> 00:40:47,612
DOCTOR: We've found something.

606
00:40:47,695 --> 00:40:51,240
It looks like metal, like some sort of seal.

607
00:40:51,324 --> 00:40:54,744
I've got a nasty feeling
the word might be "trap door”.

608
00:40:54,869 --> 00:40:57,747
Not a good word, trap door.
Never met a trap door I liked.

609
00:40:57,830 --> 00:41:00,083
IDA: The edge is covered
with those symbols.

610
00:41:00,208 --> 00:41:03,628
-ZACK: Do you think it opens?
-That's what trap doors tend to do.

611
00:41:03,711 --> 00:41:07,382
Trap door doesn't do it justice.
It's massive, Zack.

612
00:41:08,925 --> 00:41:12,679
-About 30 feet in diameter.
-ZACK: Any way of opening it?

613
00:41:12,804 --> 00:41:16,391
Don't know.
I can't see any sort of mechanism.

614
00:41:16,474 --> 00:41:19,686
DOCTOR: I suppose that's the writing.
It would tell us what to do.

615
00:41:19,769 --> 00:41:22,563
The letters that defy translation.

616
00:41:22,689 --> 00:41:24,857
Toby, did you get anywhere
with decoding it?

617
00:41:24,983 --> 00:41:28,361
Toby, they need to know. That lettering,
does it make any sort of sense?

618
00:41:28,444 --> 00:41:30,029
I know what it says.

619
00:41:30,113 --> 00:41:31,614
Then tell them.

620
00:41:31,739 --> 00:41:35,451
-When did you work that out?
-It doesn't matter, just tell them!

621
00:41:35,576 --> 00:41:38,955
(DISTORTED VOICE)
These are the words of the Beast.

622
00:41:39,080 --> 00:41:41,582
And he has woken.

623
00:41:41,666 --> 00:41:44,210
He is the heart that beats in the darkness.

624
00:41:44,293 --> 00:41:46,629
He is the blood that will never cease.

625
00:41:46,838 --> 00:41:48,923
And now he will rise.

626
00:41:49,424 --> 00:41:52,301
Officer, you will stand down. Stand down!

627
00:41:52,385 --> 00:41:56,305
What is it? What's he done?
What's happening? Rose, what's going on?

628
00:41:56,431 --> 00:41:58,433
Jefferson, report.

629
00:41:58,975 --> 00:42:00,184
Report!

630
00:42:00,268 --> 00:42:02,061
Officer, you have compromised security.

631
00:42:02,145 --> 00:42:05,273
You will stand down
and be confined. Immediately!

632
00:42:05,356 --> 00:42:10,319
Mr Jefferson, tell me, sir...
did your wife ever forgive you?

633
00:42:12,572 --> 00:42:14,073
I don't know what you mean.

634
00:42:14,157 --> 00:42:16,117
Let me tell you a secret.

635
00:42:17,201 --> 00:42:18,870
She never did.

636
00:42:20,621 --> 00:42:24,292
Officer, you will stand down
and be confined.

637
00:42:25,043 --> 00:42:26,461
Or what?

638
00:42:26,544 --> 00:42:30,131
Or under the strictures of Condition Red,
I am authorised to shoot you.

639
00:42:30,256 --> 00:42:32,508
But how many can you kill?

640
00:42:52,695 --> 00:42:55,823
THE OOD: We are the legion of the Beast.

641
00:42:57,492 --> 00:42:59,702
Rose, what is it? Rose?

642
00:43:00,703 --> 00:43:04,207
-I'm going back up.
-ZACK: Report! Report!

643
00:43:04,832 --> 00:43:06,626
Jefferson, report!

644
00:43:07,001 --> 00:43:08,920
Someone report!

645
00:43:11,172 --> 00:43:16,344
The legion shall be many
and the legion shall be few.

646
00:43:16,511 --> 00:43:17,804
It's the Ood.

647
00:43:17,887 --> 00:43:20,556
Sir, we have contamination of the livestock.

648
00:43:20,681 --> 00:43:23,309
Doctor, I don't know what it is.
It's like they're possessed.

649
00:43:23,392 --> 00:43:25,478
They won't listen to us.

650
00:43:25,603 --> 00:43:29,774
THE OOD: He has woven himself
in the fabric of your life

651
00:43:29,857 --> 00:43:32,151
since the dawn of time.

652
00:43:32,819 --> 00:43:35,071
Some may call him Abbadon.

653
00:43:35,154 --> 00:43:38,116
Some may call him Krop Tor.

654
00:43:38,741 --> 00:43:41,994
Some may call him Satan or Lucifer.

655
00:43:42,078 --> 00:43:44,288
Captain, it's the Ood. They're out of control.

656
00:43:44,372 --> 00:43:49,293
...the King of Despair, the Deathless Prince.

657
00:43:49,377 --> 00:43:51,629
The Bringer of Night.

658
00:43:54,423 --> 00:43:58,886
And these are the words
that shall set him free.

659
00:43:59,887 --> 00:44:01,514
Back up to the door!

660
00:44:01,597 --> 00:44:04,642
-I am become manifest.
-Move quickly!

661
00:44:04,725 --> 00:44:07,145
-I shall walk in the light.
-To the door!

662
00:44:07,228 --> 00:44:11,566
And my legions will swarm across worlds.

663
00:44:22,076 --> 00:44:24,745
Doctor, it's opening!

664
00:44:28,040 --> 00:44:29,625
We're moving!

665
00:44:29,709 --> 00:44:34,046
The whole thing's moving,
the planet's moving.

666
00:44:54,567 --> 00:44:59,280
I am the sin and the temptation
and the desire.

667
00:44:59,488 --> 00:45:02,867
I am the pain and the loss
and the death of hope.

668
00:45:02,950 --> 00:45:04,827
JEFFERSON: Get that door open!

669
00:45:13,211 --> 00:45:15,880
The gravity field, it's going!

670
00:45:16,631 --> 00:45:18,466
We're losing orbit!

671
00:45:20,635 --> 00:45:22,887
We're gonna fall into the black hole!

672
00:45:27,516 --> 00:45:31,145
I have been imprisoned for eternity.

673
00:45:31,979 --> 00:45:33,606
But no more.

674
00:45:34,148 --> 00:45:36,192
COMPUTER: Door sealed. Door sealed.

675
00:45:38,527 --> 00:45:40,780
BEAST: The Pit is open

676
00:45:41,822 --> 00:45:45,409
and I am free!

677
00:45:45,660 --> 00:45:47,912
(BEAST LAUGHING)

678
00:46:43,718 --> 00:46:46,220
DANNY: It's the Ood. They've gone mad.

679
00:46:50,224 --> 00:46:53,060
Doctor, can you hear me?
Doctor, Ida, are you there?

680
00:46:53,144 --> 00:46:54,353
ZACK: Danny, turn right.

681
00:46:54,437 --> 00:46:57,064
That thing is playing on very basic fears.

682
00:47:00,735 --> 00:47:02,528
-The cable's snapped.
-Get out!

683
00:47:06,032 --> 00:47:09,952
You will die and I will live.

